{"title_page": "Infinity (de Rivera)", "text_new": "{{Infobox artwork\n| image_file         = Infinity-rivera.jpg\n| painting_alignment = Front\n| image_upright      = 1\n| title              = Infinity\n| alt                =\n| other_language_1   = \n| other_title_1      = \n| other_language_2   = \n| other_title_2      =\n| artist             = Jos\u00e9 de Rivera\n| year               = 1967\n| type               = sculpture\n| height_metric      =\n| width_metric       =\n| length_metric      =\n| height_imperial    = 13.5\n| width_imperial     = 8\n| length_imperial    = 16\n| metric_unit        = m\n| imperial_unit      = ft\n| city               = Washington, D.C.\n| museum             = [[National Museum of American History]]\n| coordinates        = {{coord| 38.890844| -77.03004}}\n| owner              = Smithsonian Institution }}\n\n'''''Infinity''''' is an abstract sculpture designed by [[Jos\u00e9 de Rivera]] and created by [[Roy Gussow]]. It is located at the south entrance of the [[National Museum of American History]], at Madison Drive and 12th Street, [[Northwest, Washington, D.C.]]\n\nIt was dedicated on March 28, 1967. It cost $104,520. It slowly rotates on its base.<ref>[http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=all&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!377926~!0#focus \"Infinity, (sculpture)\"]. ''SIRIS''</ref>\n\nRivera created a similar sister sculpture that was installed at [[Rochester Institute of Technology]] one year later.<ref>[https://artoncampus.rit.edu/art/39/]''RIT Art on Campus''</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of public art in Washington, D.C., Ward 2]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20100609222757/http://americanhistory.si.edu/about/pubs/shayt-1.pdf \"Measuring Infinity: Jos\u00e9 de Rivera's Smithsonian Sculpture on the National Mall\"], ''Curator'', David Shayt, 15 January 2010\n*http://dcmemorials.com/index_indiv0000497.htm\n*http://www.aaa.si.edu/collections/interviews/oral-history-interview-jos-de-rivera-12594\n\n{{Public art in Washington, D.C.|state=collapsed}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Infinity}}\n[[Category:Modernist sculpture]]\n[[Category:1967 sculptures]]\n[[Category:Sculptures of the Smithsonian Institution]]\n[[Category:Abstract sculptures in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:Outdoor sculptures in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:Stainless steel sculptures]]\n[[Category:Steel sculptures in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:Northwest (Washington, D.C.)]]\n\n{{-}}\n{{sculpture-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox artwork\n| image_file = Infinity-rivera.jpg\n| painting_alignment = Front\n| image_size         = 300px\n| title              = Infinity\n| alt                =\n| other_language_1   = \n| other_title_1      = \n| other_language_2   = \n| other_title_2      =\n| artist             = [[Jose de Rivera]]\n| year               = 1967\n| type               = sculpture\n| height_metric      =\n| width_metric       =\n| length_metric      =\n| height_imperial    = 13.5\n| width_imperial     = 8\n| length_imperial    = 16\n| metric_unit        = m\n| imperial_unit      = ft\n| city               = Washington, D.C.\n| museum             = [[National Museum of American History]]\n| coordinates        = {{coord| 38.890844| -77.03004}}\n| owner              = Smithsonian Institution }}\n\n'''''Infinity''''' is an abstract sculpture designed by [[Jose de Rivera]] and created by [[Roy Gussow]]. It is located at the south entrance of the [[National Museum of American History]], at Madison Drive and 12th Street, [[Northwest, Washington, D.C.]]\n\nIt was dedicated on March 28, 1967. It cost $104,520. It slowly rotates on its base.\n<ref>[http://siris-artinventories.si.edu/ipac20/ipac.jsp?&profile=all&source=~!siartinventories&uri=full=3100001~!377926~!0#focus \"Infinity, (sculpture)\"]. ''SIRIS''</ref>\n\nRivera created a similar sister sculpture that was installed at [[Rochester Institute of Technology]] one year later.<ref>[https://artoncampus.rit.edu/art/39/]''RIT Art on Campus''</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of public art in Washington, D.C., Ward 2]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20100609222757/http://americanhistory.si.edu/about/pubs/shayt-1.pdf \"Measuring Infinity: Jos\u00e9 de Rivera's Smithsonian Sculpture on the National Mall\"], ''Curator'', David Shayt, 15 January 2010\n*http://dcmemorials.com/index_indiv0000497.htm\nhttp://www.aaa.si.edu/collections/interviews/oral-history-interview-jos-de-rivera-12594\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Infinity}}\n[[Category:Modernist sculpture]]\n[[Category:1967 sculptures]]\n[[Category:Sculptures of the Smithsonian Institution]]\n[[Category:Abstract sculptures in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:Outdoor sculptures in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:Stainless steel sculptures]]\n[[Category:Steel sculptures in Washington, D.C.]]\n[[Category:Northwest (Washington, D.C.)]]\n\n{{-}}\n{{sculpture-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ham II", "label": "safe", "comment": "+Template:Public art in Washington, D.C.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infinity_(de_Rivera)"}
